The embedding similarity test shows reasonable cosine similarities (0.65-0.70), confirming the wte embeddings are stored correctly as [vocab][768]. The embeddings and tokenization are both correct. The issue is definitively in the transformer layers' weight interpretation. Let me check the c_attn weight structure directly.

{
  "analysis": "Embeddings are confirmed correct (cosine similarities 0.65-0.70 for nearest neighbors). Tokenization confirmed correct. The bug is in transformer layer weight interpretation. Let me directly examine the c_attn weight matrix structure - check if a single attention computation produces reasonable Q/K/V by examining the weight at the expected offset.",
  "plan": "Check the c_attn weight values at layer 0 to determine if they're [768,2304] row-major or column-major, by examining value patterns.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/wcheck.c << 'CEOF'
#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
#include<math.h>
#define C 768
#define V 50257
float*W;
int main(int argc,char**argv){
FILE*f=fopen(argv[1],"rb");fseek(f,0,SEEK_END);long sz=ftell(f);fseek(f,0,SEEK_SET);
W=malloc(sz);fread(W,1,sz,f);fclose(f);
long base=39383808;
/* layer 0: ln1_g(768) ln1_b(768) then c_attn_w */
float*aw=W+base+1536;
/* If [768,2304] row-major: aw[i*2304+j], row i has 2304 values */
/* Check norm of each 'row' interpretation */
printf("As [768,2304] rows (in,out):\n");
for(int r=0;r<3;r++){float n=0;for(int j=0;j<2304;j++)n+=aw[r*2304+j]*aw[r*2304+j];printf("  row %d rms=%.4f\n",r,sqrtf(n/2304));}
printf("As [2304,768] rows (out,in):\n");
for(int r=0;r<3;r++){float n=0;for(int j=0;j<768;j++)n+=aw[r*768+j]*aw[r*768+j];printf("  row %d rms=%.4f\n",r,sqrtf(n/768));}
/* Check c_attn bias - first 768 should be Q bias, often near 0; values */
float*ab=aw+768*2304;
printf("c_attn_b first 6: ");for(int i=0;i<6;i++)printf("%.4f ",ab[i]);printf("\n");
printf("c_attn_b[768..773] (K?): ");for(int i=768;i<774;i++)printf("%.4f ",ab[i]);printf("\n");
return 0;}
CEOF
gcc -O3 -o /app/wcheck /app/wcheck.c -lm 2>&1 | grep error; /app/wcheck gpt2-124M.ckpt 2>&1 | grep -v warn
",
      "duration": 5.0
    }
  ]
